Bitcoin halvings also tend to get a large amount of publicity from mainstream media social media and other places where people can be influenced to purchase Bitcoin. More people learning about Bitcoin and investing in it causes the price to rise because of increased demand.

Additionally miners tend to hold the Bitcoin that they mined because it isn't as profitable for them to sell it immediately after the Bitcoin halving when they can sell it for a greater profit at an all-time high. This stops Bitcoin's price from lowering post-halving.

This halving in the Bitcoin mining reward will cause the current supply of Bitcoin being mined to be half of what it was before. Assuming that the demand for Bitcoin post-halving stays the same if it doesn't increase the price of Bitcoin will rise because more people want it.
